{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GoCAQyMeq3C94MiaAxsip8","type":"tool_result","content":"   120→- Default referrer share: **1000 bps of the total fee (= 50 bps of wager)**\n   121→- On a 1 SOL wager: total fee = 0.05 SOL (500 bps), referrer earns 0.005 SOL (1000 bps of the fee)\n   122→- Source: platform fee — no new fees charged to players\n   123→- Duration: **permanent** — referrer earns from their referees' games indefinitely\n   124→- Platform revenue impact: 1000 bps (10%) haircut on fee revenue from referred players (referrer share only; referee reward is non-fee-based)\n   125→\n   126→**KOL override:** Admin can set a custom referrer rate per wallet (stored in DB). This supports partnership agreements where a KOL may receive a higher share (e.g., 2000-3000 bps of total fee). Default rate applies to all non-KOL referrers.\n   127→\n   128→**Settlement hook:** After each game settles, the existing settlement worker checks if the player has a referrer → calculates earnings → inserts into `referral_earnings` table. No additional RPC calls. No on-chain changes.\n   129→\n   130→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   131→- [ ] When a referred player's game settles, the referrer's earning is calculated and stored <!-- gap: no settlement hook -->\n   132→- [ ] Default referrer rate is 1000 bps of the total fee (configurable via environment/config) <!-- gap: no config env var REFERRAL_DEFAULT_RATE_BPS -->\n   133→- [x] KOL wallets can have a custom rate set by admin (stored in `referral_kol_rates` table or equivalent) <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql creates referral_kol_rates with rate_bps, set_by, timestamps -->\n   134→- [x] Earnings are recorded per-game in `referral_earnings` with: referrer, referee, round_id, game_type, wager_lamports, earned_lamports <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql — referral_earnings table has all specified columns -->\n   135→- [x] Referrer earnings accrue indefinitely with no cap or expiry <!-- satisfied: no TTL or cap constraint in 011_referral.sql -->\n   136→\n   137→### FR-5: Earnings Dashboard & Stats\n   138→\n   139→Referrers can view their referral performance and earnings.\n   140→\n   141→**Stats view:**\n   142→- Total referred players\n   143→- Active referred players (played in last 7 days)\n   144→- Total wager volume from referrals\n   145→- Total earnings (all time)\n   146→- Pending (unclaimed) balance\n   147→- Per-game earnings log (paginated)\n   148→\n   149→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   150→- [ ] Referral page shows summary stats (referred count, active count, volume, total earned, pending balance) <!-- gap: no frontend referral page -->\n   151→- [ ] Detailed earnings log is available, paginated, showing per-game entries <!-- gap: no GET /referral/earnings endpoint -->\n   152→- [ ] Stats update in near-real-time (within settlement latency, ~3-5s) <!-- gap: no stats endpoint or settlement hook -->\n   153→- [ ] Page is accessible from main navigation or profile section <!-- gap: no sidebar nav item -->\n   154→\n   155→### FR-6: Claim Flow\n   156→\n   157→Referrers can claim their accumulated earnings. Claims are async via the event queue (FR-11) to keep SOL transfers off the request path.\n   158→\n   159→**Flow:** Player clicks \"Claim\" → backend validates balance > minimum threshold → creates claim row with status `pending` + inserts `referral.claim_requested` event in same transaction → returns 202 with claim ID → frontend polls `GET /referral/claim/:claimId` → queue worker acquires claim lock, re-verifies available balance, executes treasury transfer, writes tx signature → claim status updates to `completed` (or `failed`) → frontend shows final state.\n   160→\n   161→**Claim state machine:**\n   162→`pending -> processing -> completed`\n   163→`pending -> processing -> failed` (retryable by queue until max attempts, terminal failure only after retries exhausted)\n   164→\n   165→**Balance snapshot rule:** on claim request, backend snapshots `amount_lamports` from current pending earnings. Handler re-validates this snapshot against unclaimed earnings before transfer to prevent overpay on concurrent requests.\n   166→\n   167→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   168→- [ ] Player can claim their full pending referral balance <!-- gap: no claim endpoint or handler -->\n   169→- [ ] Claim request returns immediately (202 Accepted) with a claim ID for polling <!-- gap: no POST /referral/claim endpoint -->\n   170→- [ ] Queue worker executes the SOL transfer from treasury to player wallet <!-- gap: no claim handler registered -->\n   171→- [x] Claim is recorded with: wallet, amount_lamports, status, timestamps, tx_signature (on success) <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql — referral_claims table has all specified columns -->\n   172→- [ ] Concurrent claims from the same wallet are prevented (DB-level locking on balance snapshot) <!-- gap: no claim logic to use locking -->\n   173→- [ ] Zero-balance claims are rejected with a clear error message <!-- gap: no claim endpoint -->\n   174→- [ ] Minimum claim threshold is enforced (e.g., 0.01 SOL) to avoid dust transactions <!-- gap: no threshold config or validation -->\n   175→- [x] Failed transfers are retried by the queue (up to max_attempts) with exponential backoff <!-- satisfied: queue/worker.ts implements exponential backoff (5s→30s→300s) for all event types -->\n   176→\n   177→### FR-7: API Contract\n   178→\n   179→All referral operations are exposed via authenticated REST endpoints.\n   180→\n   181→**Error response shape (all endpoints):**\n   182→`{ error: { code: string, message: string, retryable?: boolean } }`\n   183→\n   184→```\n   185→POST /referral/code                — Set referral code\n   186→  Body: { code: string }\n   187→  Response: { code: string, url: string }\n   188→\n   189→GET  /referral/code                — Get current referral code\n   190→  Response: { code: string, url: string } | 404\n   191→\n   192→POST /referral/apply               — Apply a referral code to current user\n   193→  Body: { code: string }\n   194→  Response: { referrer: string, benefit: string }\n   195→\n   196→GET  /referral/stats               — Get referral summary stats\n   197→  Response: {\n   198→    referredCount: number,\n   199→    activeCount: number,\n   200→    totalVolumeLamports: string,\n   201→    totalEarnedLamports: string,\n   202→    pendingLamports: string\n   203→  }\n   204→\n   205→GET  /referral/earnings            — Get detailed per-game earnings log\n   206→  Query: { page?: number, limit?: number }\n   207→  Response: {\n   208→    items: [{\n   209→      roundId: string,\n   210→      gameType: string,\n   211→      refereeWallet: string,\n   212→      wagerLamports: string,\n   213→      earnedLamports: string,\n   214→      createdAt: string\n   215→    }],\n   216→    pagination: { page: number, totalPages: number }\n   217→  }\n   218→\n   219→POST /referral/claim               — Request earnings claim (async via queue)\n   220→  Response: { claimId: string, amountLamports: string, status: \"pending\" }\n   221→\n   222→GET  /referral/claim/:claimId      — Poll claim status\n   223→  Response: { claimId: string, amountLamports: string, status: \"pending\" | \"completed\" | \"failed\", txSignature?: string }\n   224→```\n   225→\n   226→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   227→- [ ] All endpoints require JWT authentication <!-- gap: no referral routes registered -->\n   228→- [ ] All endpoints return appropriate error codes (400 for bad input, 404 for not found, 409 for conflict) <!-- gap: no referral routes -->\n   229→- [ ] Rate limiting is applied to code generation and claim endpoints <!-- gap: no referral routes -->\n   230→- [ ] Monetary values use lamport strings (not floating point) <!-- gap: no API responses to verify -->\n   231→\n   232→### FR-8: Database Schema\n   233→\n   234→New tables for the referral system. All off-chain, no program changes.\n   235→\n   236→```sql\n   237→referral_codes (\n   238→  id            SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\n   239→  wallet        TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"92db3e41-1856-4eac-bac8-e2a98fa62710","uuid":"25522ffa-7e33-44cc-8ad7-2bdd4b371e8b","timestamp":"2026-03-25T12:03:49.365Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/300-referral-system/spec.md","content":"- Default referrer share: **1000 bps of the total fee (= 50 bps of wager)**\n- On a 1 SOL wager: total fee = 0.05 SOL (500 bps), referrer earns 0.005 SOL (1000 bps of the fee)\n- Source: platform fee — no new fees charged to players\n- Duration: **permanent** — referrer earns from their referees' games indefinitely\n- Platform revenue impact: 1000 bps (10%) haircut on fee revenue from referred players (referrer share only; referee reward is non-fee-based)\n\n**KOL override:** Admin can set a custom referrer rate per wallet (stored in DB). This supports partnership agreements where a KOL may receive a higher share (e.g., 2000-3000 bps of total fee). Default rate applies to all non-KOL referrers.\n\n**Settlement hook:** After each game settles, the existing settlement worker checks if the player has a referrer → calculates earnings → inserts into `referral_earnings` table. No additional RPC calls. No on-chain changes.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] When a referred player's game settles, the referrer's earning is calculated and stored <!-- gap: no settlement hook -->\n- [ ] Default referrer rate is 1000 bps of the total fee (configurable via environment/config) <!-- gap: no config env var REFERRAL_DEFAULT_RATE_BPS -->\n- [x] KOL wallets can have a custom rate set by admin (stored in `referral_kol_rates` table or equivalent) <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql creates referral_kol_rates with rate_bps, set_by, timestamps -->\n- [x] Earnings are recorded per-game in `referral_earnings` with: referrer, referee, round_id, game_type, wager_lamports, earned_lamports <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql — referral_earnings table has all specified columns -->\n- [x] Referrer earnings accrue indefinitely with no cap or expiry <!-- satisfied: no TTL or cap constraint in 011_referral.sql -->\n\n### FR-5: Earnings Dashboard & Stats\n\nReferrers can view their referral performance and earnings.\n\n**Stats view:**\n- Total referred players\n- Active referred players (played in last 7 days)\n- Total wager volume from referrals\n- Total earnings (all time)\n- Pending (unclaimed) balance\n- Per-game earnings log (paginated)\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Referral page shows summary stats (referred count, active count, volume, total earned, pending balance) <!-- gap: no frontend referral page -->\n- [ ] Detailed earnings log is available, paginated, showing per-game entries <!-- gap: no GET /referral/earnings endpoint -->\n- [ ] Stats update in near-real-time (within settlement latency, ~3-5s) <!-- gap: no stats endpoint or settlement hook -->\n- [ ] Page is accessible from main navigation or profile section <!-- gap: no sidebar nav item -->\n\n### FR-6: Claim Flow\n\nReferrers can claim their accumulated earnings. Claims are async via the event queue (FR-11) to keep SOL transfers off the request path.\n\n**Flow:** Player clicks \"Claim\" → backend validates balance > minimum threshold → creates claim row with status `pending` + inserts `referral.claim_requested` event in same transaction → returns 202 with claim ID → frontend polls `GET /referral/claim/:claimId` → queue worker acquires claim lock, re-verifies available balance, executes treasury transfer, writes tx signature → claim status updates to `completed` (or `failed`) → frontend shows final state.\n\n**Claim state machine:**\n`pending -> processing -> completed`\n`pending -> processing -> failed` (retryable by queue until max attempts, terminal failure only after retries exhausted)\n\n**Balance snapshot rule:** on claim request, backend snapshots `amount_lamports` from current pending earnings. Handler re-validates this snapshot against unclaimed earnings before transfer to prevent overpay on concurrent requests.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Player can claim their full pending referral balance <!-- gap: no claim endpoint or handler -->\n- [ ] Claim request returns immediately (202 Accepted) with a claim ID for polling <!-- gap: no POST /referral/claim endpoint -->\n- [ ] Queue worker executes the SOL transfer from treasury to player wallet <!-- gap: no claim handler registered -->\n- [x] Claim is recorded with: wallet, amount_lamports, status, timestamps, tx_signature (on success) <!-- satisfied: 011_referral.sql — referral_claims table has all specified columns -->\n- [ ] Concurrent claims from the same wallet are prevented (DB-level locking on balance snapshot) <!-- gap: no claim logic to use locking -->\n- [ ] Zero-balance claims are rejected with a clear error message <!-- gap: no claim endpoint -->\n- [ ] Minimum claim threshold is enforced (e.g., 0.01 SOL) to avoid dust transactions <!-- gap: no threshold config or validation -->\n- [x] Failed transfers are retried by the queue (up to max_attempts) with exponential backoff <!-- satisfied: queue/worker.ts implements exponential backoff (5s→30s→300s) for all event types -->\n\n### FR-7: API Contract\n\nAll referral operations are exposed via authenticated REST endpoints.\n\n**Error response shape (all endpoints):**\n`{ error: { code: string, message: string, retryable?: boolean } }`\n\n```\nPOST /referral/code                — Set referral code\n  Body: { code: string }\n  Response: { code: string, url: string }\n\nGET  /referral/code                — Get current referral code\n  Response: { code: string, url: string } | 404\n\nPOST /referral/apply               — Apply a referral code to current user\n  Body: { code: string }\n  Response: { referrer: string, benefit: string }\n\nGET  /referral/stats               — Get referral summary stats\n  Response: {\n    referredCount: number,\n    activeCount: number,\n    totalVolumeLamports: string,\n    totalEarnedLamports: string,\n    pendingLamports: string\n  }\n\nGET  /referral/earnings            — Get detailed per-game earnings log\n  Query: { page?: number, limit?: number }\n  Response: {\n    items: [{\n      roundId: string,\n      gameType: string,\n      refereeWallet: string,\n      wagerLamports: string,\n      earnedLamports: string,\n      createdAt: string\n    }],\n    pagination: { page: number, totalPages: number }\n  }\n\nPOST /referral/claim               — Request earnings claim (async via queue)\n  Response: { claimId: string, amountLamports: string, status: \"pending\" }\n\nGET  /referral/claim/:claimId      — Poll claim status\n  Response: { claimId: string, amountLamports: string, status: \"pending\" | \"completed\" | \"failed\", txSignature?: string }\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] All endpoints require JWT authentication <!-- gap: no referral routes registered -->\n- [ ] All endpoints return appropriate error codes (400 for bad input, 404 for not found, 409 for conflict) <!-- gap: no referral routes -->\n- [ ] Rate limiting is applied to code generation and claim endpoints <!-- gap: no referral routes -->\n- [ ] Monetary values use lamport strings (not floating point) <!-- gap: no API responses to verify -->\n\n### FR-8: Database Schema\n\nNew tables for the referral system. All off-chain, no program changes.\n\n```sql\nreferral_codes (\n  id            SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,\n  wallet        TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,","numLines":120,"startLine":120,"totalLines":715}}}
